'''''Sangliana''''' is a 1988 [[Kannada language|Kannada]] [[cult]] [[action drama]] film directed, co-produced and written by P. Nanjundappa in [[India]]. It is loosely inspired by the life story of the cop-turned-politician [[H. T. Sangliana]]. The film stars [[Shankar Nag]], [[Bhavya]] and [[Tara (Kannada actress)|Tara]] in lead roles, with actor [[Ambareesh]] making a special appearance.<ref>[http://www.nthwall.com/ka/crew/S-P-Sangliyana-1988-cast-and-crew/9219803277 Cast & Crew] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503083921/http://www.nthwall.com/ka/crew/S-P-Sangliyana-1988-cast-and-crew/9219803277 |date=3 May 2014 }}</ref> The film was produced under "Pushpagiri Films" banner and the music was composed by [[Hamsalekha]].

The film was a ''Superhit'' upon release and a sequel to this was made from the same cast and crew and released as ''[[S. P. Sangliyana Part 2]]'' in 1990. A third movie titled ''[[Sangliyana Part-3]]'', which starred Devaraj in lead role was released in 1997.

== Cast ==
* [[Shankar Nag]] - Sangliyana 
* [[Bhavya]] - Kanchana 
* [[Ambareesh]] - Inspector Amar (extended cameo appearance)
* [[Devaraj]] - Vikram(Vikki)
* [[Tara (Kannada actress)|Tara]] - Wife of forest officer
* [[Srinath]] - DGP
* [[Vajramuni]] - Nagappa 
* [[Master Manjunath]] - Avinash 
* [[Disco Shanti]] - Pub Dancer
* [[Doddanna]]- Kalle Gowda
* [[Lohithaswa]] - Mahesh (father of Kanchana)
* Sudheer - Kumbi
* Gayatri Prabhakar - Wife of Kalle Gowda
* Prathiba - Keep of Kalle Gowda
* Ramesh Kamath - Forest officer

